The Benelli Super Black Eagle II Semi-Auto Shotgun sets the standard for high performance and versatility in semi-automatic shotguns meant for hardcore hunting. Benelli manufactures all Super Black eagle barrels and choke tubes with their Crio® System, which creates an even-grained, slick surface resulting in less resistance against wads and shot for uniform shot patterns and cleaner barrels.

title: For Sale:  Charles Lancaster Boxlock 12GA
postcontent: Charles Lancaster O-grade boxlock 12 gauge self-opening ejector shotgun. Built in 1889 according to factory letter.  28" sleeved barrels choked IC and light modified (by gauge), 2.5" chambers.  Sleeving done by E.C. Ashthorpe of Severn Stoke, Worcester, and the seam is nearly invisible.  Approximate dimensions: 14" LOP to front trigger, 1.5" DAC, 2" DAH, ~3/16" cast off.  6lb. 7oz and very well balanced.  Features Lancaster's distinctive vine-leaf engraving.  Very good condition but does show a bit of bluing wear on the floor plate and muzzle.  Includes Jeff's Outfitters canvas and leather case with accessories and reproduction trade label.  I also have a flat of assorted 2.5 inch shells which I can include at extra cost.  May consider trade for Darne slide action shotgun, or partial trade for Walther PPK or Colt New Frontier 22/22WMR convertible. Delivery to front range area possible.  Scammers and lowballers will be ignored.  While not as well known in America, Lancaster made guns of similar quality to Holland & Holland, Purdey, and Boss.  Annie Oakley owned four Lancasters.  The O-grade is a unique boxlock built on Frederick Beesley's patent self-opening mechanism, similar to Purdey's self opening sidelock which was also invented by Beesley.  Most London gunmakers outsourced production of their boxlocks to the bigger Birmingham firms; it has been suggested that Lancaster's O-grade was so named because it was built by Charles Osborne.  Many more photos available on request.
